//
// test/preprocess/p06/fail.test — P6 violation: a compile-time
// helper call appearing OUTSIDE both valid contexts (a `#define`
// body and an `#if` condition) per FR-018 +
// `docs/spec/nsl_pp.ebnf` notes section + the FR-037 locked-string
// table in
// `specs/002-m1-lex-preprocess/contracts/diagnostic-output.contract.md`.
//
// FR-037 P6 lock:
//   `compile-time helper '_<NAME>' used outside #define / #if condition`
//
// For this fixture <NAME> is `pow` (the source spells the call
// `_pow(...)`), so the rendered diagnostic is:
//   error: compile-time helper '_pow' used outside #define / #if condition
//
// Per Constitution Principle VIII the failing fixture asserts the
// EXACT diagnostic string. Renaming or weakening it later requires a
// contract amendment in `contracts/diagnostic-output.contract.md`
// PLUS this fixture's update in the same change.
//
// Source: a `_pow(...)` call sits on a passthrough line — neither
// inside a `#define` body nor inside an `#if` condition. The
// preprocessor MUST detect this at preprocess time and MUST NOT
// allow the helper-call tokens to cross the seam (P12).
//
// **RED state**: against the unchanged Phase-3 tree the lexer
// tokenizes `_pow` as `tk_system_function` and exits 0; no
// preprocessor exists to detect the P6 violation. Phase-4 wires the
// detection.

// RUN: echo 'reg x = _pow(2.0, 4.0);' > %t.nsl
// RUN: not %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl 2>&1 | FileCheck %s

// FR-037 LOCKED STRING — exact match:
// CHECK: error: compile-time helper '_pow' used outside #define / #if condition
